defaultWHAT defaultGOVERNMENT HASdefault ANNOUNCEDdefault&#xa0;default“The Government will secure the universal postal service for the benefit of all users by securing Royal Mail’s future through the introduction of private sector capital and associate disciplines. 
defaultThis will be achieved through:
default
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultdelivering a sale of shares in Royal Mail within this Parliament;
default
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultcreating an employee share scheme that, as Parliament has decided, will lead to at least 10% of the company in employee ownership, to drive stronger staff engagement; and
default
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultdelivering a financial outcome for the taxpayer, which when considered in the context of the overarching policy objective, represents overall value for money.”
